00:06:40.576 --> 00:06:44.456
So we are not talking perhaps about a model or a tool that somebody can use,

106
00:06:44.896 --> 00:06:48.796
but we are actually talking about an agent, a co-scientist, an

107
00:06:48.896 --> 00:06:52.836
active partner in research that helps us plan,

108
00:06:53.016 --> 00:06:56.536
act, debug our experiments, verify them,

109
00:06:56.936 --> 00:07:00.736
and also iterate. That we go from observations

110
00:07:01.176 --> 00:07:04.976
to hypothesis to experimental validation of

111
00:07:05.036 --> 00:07:08.136
those hypotheses. And we close this loop and we can

112
00:07:09.116 --> 00:07:13.016
run it faster, more reliably, and with greater

113
00:07:13.026 --> 00:07:13.816
transparency.

114
00:07:16.136 --> 00:07:19.796
So the goal is to speed up scientific discovery dramatically.

115
00:07:20.276 --> 00:07:23.656
Create a virtual scientist that helps us

116
00:07:23.676 --> 00:07:25.536
automate scientific research,

117
00:07:26.976 --> 00:07:28.836
suggest and explore novel hypothesis,

118
00:07:29.636 --> 00:07:31.496
perform tasks much faster,

119
00:07:32.816 --> 00:07:36.476
and importantly, tackle many tasks at the same time.

120
00:07:36.856 --> 00:07:40.316
So really parallelize and speed up the entire

121
00:07:40.416 --> 00:07:41.156
discovery loop.

122
00:07:42.876 --> 00:07:46.826
And if we look at how scientists do research and discovery today,

123
00:07:46.976 --> 00:07:49.716
how we work, it's actually extremely fragmented.

124
00:07:50.196 --> 00:07:53.976
We read research papers, we collect and process data, we

125
00:07:54.096 --> 00:07:57.696
run experiments and log them. We order some

126
00:07:57.736 --> 00:08:01.496
materials, perhaps design some molecules, write some

