00:15:28.680 --> 00:15:32.460
operator talks to it and gives it a task, uploads the data,

253
00:15:32.580 --> 00:15:36.480
could be terabytes of data, and then talks to it what it wants to

254
00:15:36.520 --> 00:15:40.440
do. And the agent, what it's going to do is actually first going to

255
00:15:40.500 --> 00:15:41.460
enter in a planning

256
00:15:42.440 --> 00:15:46.400
stage, where together with the human scientist, they are planning

257
00:15:46.480 --> 00:15:50.200
out the steps to execute or complete that task.

258
00:15:50.510 --> 00:15:54.460
So it's a collaborative process about what are the steps that need to be

259
00:15:54.560 --> 00:15:54.980
taken

260
00:15:55.920 --> 00:15:58.940
to potentially complete the task.

261
00:15:59.260 --> 00:16:03.000
And this is where the collaboration between human and the agent is

262
00:16:03.060 --> 00:16:07.020
happening so that the agent is not going off the rails and do something

263
00:16:07.100 --> 00:16:09.160
strange, but it's actually a collaborative

264
00:16:10.260 --> 00:16:13.080
effort for the human scientist and the agent

265
00:16:13.940 --> 00:16:17.880
to decide on the plan about how to complete

266
00:16:17.960 --> 00:16:21.840
the task. And then as the agent goes and executes on the plan,

267
00:16:22.220 --> 00:16:25.260
the plan is tracked along the entire process.

268
00:16:26.100 --> 00:16:29.980
And also the agent can go back to the human scientist and say, "Hey, based on

269
00:16:30.020 --> 00:16:33.770
my results, I want to enter into a replanning stage." And

270
00:16:33.820 --> 00:16:37.300
again, it's a collaborative effort to do that replanning step.

271
00:16:39.020 --> 00:16:42.820
And the reason I'm mentioning this, because when we were designing Biomi, it

272
00:16:42.880 --> 00:16:46.620
was very important for us, for the human scientist to be at the

273
00:16:46.660 --> 00:16:50.340
steering wheel. We wanted to design the system in such a way

274
00:16:50.380 --> 00:16:52.940
that it's truly a collaborative experience.

275
00:16:53.380 --> 00:16:57.340
And the important aspect of why we want to do it this way is

276
00:16:57.360 --> 00:17:01.260
because large language models are notoriously unreliable,

277
00:17:01.680 --> 00:17:05.300
non-deterministic, and they hallucinate all the time. Right?

278
00:17:05.340 --> 00:17:09.040
You can ask the same question multiple times, and you are going to get

279
00:17:09.050 --> 00:17:12.990
different answers each time. So the way we solve this

280
00:17:13.040 --> 00:17:14.220
is that

281
00:17:15.220 --> 00:17:18.161
Biomi actually asks clarification questions,

282
00:17:18.600 --> 00:17:22.500
brainstorms with the human scientists with follow-ups,

283
00:17:23.580 --> 00:17:27.520
and then iterates and aligns on the plan for each it

284
00:17:27.580 --> 00:17:31.440
executes. What is also important that as the human

285
00:17:31.600 --> 00:17:35.140
and the Biomi agent collaborate, the Biomi agent

286
00:17:35.180 --> 00:17:39.120
continually learns from the scientist, that it extracts

287
00:17:39.200 --> 00:17:42.910
scientists' preferences, scientists' intent, and

288
00:17:42.980 --> 00:17:46.480
just the ways how the human scientist likes to

289
00:17:46.540 --> 00:17:50.280
run certain processes. So this means that over

290
00:17:50.320 --> 00:17:53.800
time, each scientist builds their own personalized virtual

291
00:17:54.300 --> 00:17:58.020
research collaborator that actually knows them, knows their preference,

292
00:17:58.300 --> 00:18:00.240
knows their ways of doing work.

293
00:18:01.320 --> 00:18:05.009
So this notion of scientific rigor and trust is really

294
00:18:05.040 --> 00:18:09.020
important to us because in Biomi, every

295
00:18:09.080 --> 00:18:13.040
agent step is fully transparent and reproducible.

296
00:18:13.740 --> 00:18:17.340
The agent self-reviews the intermediate steps and

297
00:18:17.380 --> 00:18:21.160
validates them. And we have a number of deterministic guardrail

298
00:18:21.260 --> 00:18:22.740
systems that take

299
00:18:24.020 --> 00:18:26.880
care of the safety and prevent

300
00:18:26.920 --> 00:18:30.828
hallucination.What is also important that whenever the

301
00:18:30.888 --> 00:18:34.568
