1482
01:30:41.030 --> 01:30:44.090
Innova, and what you'll see is a very diverse set of systems.

1483
01:30:44.130 --> 01:30:47.890
Systems with a large community system, systems that are premier academic

1484
01:30:47.910 --> 01:30:51.740
medical centers, systems that are regional

1485
01:30:51.910 --> 01:30:55.390
community hospitals, which means we're not just thinking of AI

1486
01:30:55.890 --> 01:30:59.730
as the kind of thing that is implemented for the wealthiest

1487
01:30:59.750 --> 01:31:03.150
hospitals or the most pristine hospitals, but we really want to bring it in a

1488
01:31:03.230 --> 01:31:06.550
way that we can bring this value to very diverse

1489
01:31:06.570 --> 01:31:09.030
populations and very diverse

1490
01:31:10.410 --> 01:31:14.350
settings. And if anyone is interested in learning more

1491
01:31:14.390 --> 01:31:18.370
or talking to me more about it or collaborating, here's my email address if

1492
01:31:18.410 --> 01:31:22.370
you'd like me to send an email. And I'll be around between

1493
01:31:22.410 --> 01:31:26.270
the opening of G and H outside if you'd

1494
01:31:26.310 --> 01:31:29.990
like to talk more for the next couple of hours. Thank you so much.

1495
01:31:39.660 --> 01:31:43.530
That was very impressive, I think, and we've seen how these technologies can not

1496
01:31:43.580 --> 01:31:47.100
just be developed, but also actually brought to clinical practice.

1497
01:31:47.720 --> 01:31:51.600
And now it's my great pleasure to introduce the final speaker of this

